00:00:07.750 --> 00:00:13.470
&gt;&gt; BARD Express: Browsing
the BARD Collection.

00:00:13.470 --> 00:00:19.210
&gt;&gt; Judy: Hello, I'm Judy Dixon,
Consumer Relations Officer at NLS.

00:00:19.210 --> 00:00:23.180
In this edition of the
BARD Express How-To Series,

00:00:23.180 --> 00:00:27.350
I'm going to cover browsing
the BARD collection.

00:00:27.350 --> 00:00:32.010
BARD Express gives you many options
for browsing available materials.

00:00:32.010 --> 00:00:37.700
You can browse by series, browse
by subject, or browse magazines.

00:00:37.700 --> 00:00:42.300
To browse by series, from the BARD
Express Main Menu select browse

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:43.600
by series.

00:00:43.600 --> 00:00:45.350
You will be presented with a list

00:00:45.350 --> 00:00:49.340
of series available in
the BARD collection.

00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:51.960
Note that you are going to
land in the list of series

00:00:51.960 --> 00:00:54.390
and the focus will be
on the first series

00:00:54.390 --> 00:00:57.020
in the list of more than 4,000.

00:00:57.020 --> 00:01:01.210
To find a particular series,
tab to the edit box and type

00:01:01.210 --> 00:01:03.270
in the name of the series.

00:01:03.270 --> 00:01:08.830
For example, I am going to
search for the Alex Cross Series.

00:01:08.830 --> 00:01:13.340
Tab to the list of series
containing the words Alex Cross

00:01:13.340 --> 00:01:18.560 position:56%
and use the arrow up and down keys
to find the one you are looking for.

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:23.790
Select the series title to
access the books in the series.

00:01:23.790 --> 00:01:29.250
